definition[0]: to move very quickly, often making a sound like something rushing through the air
example[1]: I saw a big piece of metal whizzing through the air.
example[2]: Let’s just whizz through it one more time.
definition[3]: someone who is very fast, intelligent, or skilled in a particular activity
definition[5]: someone who is very skilled in a particular activity or is successful in a particular area of work
example[4]: Top managers may befinancial whizzes, but they aren’t marketing geniuses.
example[5]: He’s a whizz at website design.
